Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.78,0:00:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,what it takes to make people stop talking 100 decibels the calibrated\Nenergy of that music is 700 so I just wanted to know what 700 sounds like it's
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.22,0:00:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,like being in shark Cathedral Notre Dame the same energy 700 hmm well let's see\Nwhat were we explained this morning Oh secret of the universe some things are
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.32,0:01:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,very simple once you understand the truth of them and the great mystery and\Ndissertation over the centuries falls apart so on the blackboard here on the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.41,0:01:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,whiteboard we have a picture of God as indicated by these little dots the\Nlittle dots are just so you notice that the board is actually white and in the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.28,0:01:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,middle we have the ego so as you see the ego is form\Nthe
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.38,0:01:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the\Nthe ego is form the ego is form and spirit is the formless so spirit is the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.28,0:01:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,field and the ego is the content of the field the content of the field\Ntherefore the content of the field cannot be understood unless you define
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.60,0:02:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,what the time context is so no truth is definable unless you describe the\Nparameters of the context in which it's being described because that
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.89,0:02:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,which seems to be true in one context is a lie and another it's an it's not\Npossible to define truth without without stating the context without staying the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.99,0:02:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,context and that is a great source of philosophic and intellectual error\Nscientific error is the failure to define the context in which a certain
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.43,0:02:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,thing is being said you mentioned this morning\Nprojecting current social more ease backwards in time and then making them
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.97,0:02:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,wrong is one of the defects of faults of logic because what's true now is true\Nbecause of the field the social consciousness that is an awareness that
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.09,0:03:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,prevails today but that was not so in past times yeah all right so let's see\Nwhere were we with our projecting slides oh my goodness we're brushing up to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.00,0:03:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,quantum mechanics oh and you see because we say that you know within the\NNewtonian paradigm or causality reigns supreme this causes this everything is
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.06,0:03:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,definable and solvable by the differential calculus\Nbut outside the realm of the definable knowable and predictable we begin to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.51,0:03:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,discover another realm another region\NThe non-linear domain, yeah, the non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.79,0:03:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is linear, but around the edge, the linear starts to get a little fuzzy.\NIt gets a little fuzzy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.88,0:04:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So quantum mechanics then takes us into the world of the fuzzy.\NYeah, the Newtonian paradigm, you see, here's the Newtonian paradigm,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.91,0:04:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the limitation of the mechanistic reductionist\Nwho is stuck with a computational, limited, permanent, constricted, settled, sequential,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.06,0:04:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,provable, highly predictable world.\NHowever, although he believes in that, he doesn't live there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.51,0:04:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He lives farther to the right in the quantum potential,\Nthe quantum potential, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.51,0:04:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,because in actuality, subjectively, things are quite disorderly.\NThey're not at all predictable.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.51,0:04:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,They're quite illogical, frankly.\NBecause they're creative, they're actually free.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.51,0:04:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not determined.\NA little bit of imagination totally changes the whole thing
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.73,0:05:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's progressive.\NThings are not separate and discrete and therefore measurable
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.76,0:05:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,without defining context\Nbecause they're intermingled and interconnected.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.89,0:05:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They're diffuse.\NThe accident that happened with, what do you call that thing that was off in the air?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.72,0:05:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Space shuttle.\NSpace shuttle.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.20,0:05:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a consequence of the field.\NIt's not within the computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.86,0:05:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the carelessness, the indifference, the somewhatness,\Nthe, oh yeah, of humankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.86,0:05:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not measurable.\NHuh.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.86,0:05:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,How many times have you taken off in your car\Nand you really should have checked the pressure in your left rear tire
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.92,0:05:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and you didn't?\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.92,0:05:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.\NIt drove me back and forth to work all week.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.24,0:05:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see, that's not measurable, though.\NCaringness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.68,0:05:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's diffuse.\NIt's vague.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.72,0:06:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's non-local.\NThings happen that are beyond comprehension.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.96,0:06:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Things don't happen separate from each other but simultaneously.\NThese things here are measurable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.08,0:06:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,These things here are observable.\NYou can measure a quantum.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.24,0:06:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But how would you measure, is it worth the bother or not\Nto check the pressure in the rear tire?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.24,0:06:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it worth the bother?\NAh, it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.24,0:06:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not immeasurable.\NYou understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.24,0:06:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, your lip just hung in the balance.\NYour lip hangs in the balance by, oh well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.24,0:06:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we could.\NAh, I'd rather have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.34,0:07:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Thousands of lives just went down the soup there, folks.\NImagine the time of invasion of, I'm not very left-brained today,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.52,0:07:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the great invasion of Germany across the English Channel,\NBritain and Normandy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.77,0:07:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And who was the German general?\NRommel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.77,0:07:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Rommel.\NRommel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.80,0:07:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Rommel was off celebrating his wife's birthday\Non the day of the great invasion,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.80,0:07:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,which the Allies likely would not have won had Rommel been there.\NBut Rommel said, okay, Christina, or whatever his name is,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.48,0:07:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,he didn't want to disappoint his wife, so he wasn't there.\NAny more than the admirals were available in Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.67,0:07:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They were off at a party someplace, I think.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.15,0:07:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Where were the great admirals?\NThe great admirals to defend Pearl Harbor on December 7th, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.28,0:08:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I think they were at a birthday party or someplace.\NSo those are the non-ponderables, the immeasurables.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.28,0:08:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And those are the things that define, decide human history, aren't they?\NThe human history is not decided by the Maginot Line.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.28,0:08:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The Maginot Line in World War II was indestructible.\NNothing could have gotten across the Maginot Line.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.56,0:08:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if I was the general on this side,\NI would have said, I will put up a Maginot Line.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.56,0:08:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That forces them to come across through the Ardennes Forest.\NSo I would have been waiting for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.66,0:08:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And wouldn't have been surprised at all.\NSo history then is set by the imponderables.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.42,0:08:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Just fleeting mood, a slight forgetfulness, a little bit of tiredness.\NYou get something in your eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.11,0:08:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Infinite possibility.\NAnd it's altered by observation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.11,0:09:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is the whole quantum mechanics.\NIt's altered by observation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.72,0:09:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody interested in explanation of the quantum mechanics\Nand how it applies to consciousness?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.72,0:09:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Raise your hand.\NOh my goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.72,0:09:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, we will show that after all.\NOkay, it's expansive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.72,0:09:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with context.\NSo the field then is context.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.29,0:09:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this is the world of force.\NThe Newtonian paradigm is the world of force.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.29,0:09:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Force goes from here to there.\NAnd consequently, it expends energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.77,0:09:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, it results in counter force.\NForce always results in counter force.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.09,0:09:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Force always exhausts itself.\NThe great Roman Empire dominated for a thousand years.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.83,0:09:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, it couldn't be fit anymore.\NMoney, gold, bodies, lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.83,0:10:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And it just petered out.\NThey just married the local women and the empire dissolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.83,0:10:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It just petered out.\NThe heck with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.83,0:10:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It killed so many people.\NHe just pooped from killing people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.83,0:10:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And he just falls over and says,\NThe hell with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.83,0:10:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I'll get married and raise kids.\NAnd that was the end of the Roman Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.81,0:10:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, power is like gravity.\NPower, which is like spirituality,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.53,0:10:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,influences everything within its field\Nas a consequent of that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.76,0:10:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,As a consequent of that which it is.\NSo spiritually devoted people
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.95,0:10:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,think that they're bringing about change in the world\Nby doing this and doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.95,0:10:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It has nothing to do with doing this and doing that.\NIt has to do with what you have become.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.95,0:11:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What you have become then empowers the field.\NThe field then brings about
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.95,0:11:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,certain consequences automatically\Nas a consequence of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.52,0:11:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So power does not consume energy.\NYou don't have to feed anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.52,0:11:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,any energy to gravity.\NGravity just completely controls.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.75,0:11:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It influences everything within its domain\Nand it requires no power at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.42,0:11:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It does not consume power.\NSo divinity then encompasses all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.77,0:11:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And its power is infinite.\NAnd like a great gravitational field,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.00,0:11:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,everything within it then\Nis at the effect of the power of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.25,0:11:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why divine justice is absolute,\Nimpersonal and absolute
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.20,0:12:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,as a consequence of the power and the quality\Nand the nature of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.16,0:12:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point of fearing God\Nbecause the giant electromagnet
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.32,0:12:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw out behind this building this morning,\Nevery little iron filing
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.32,0:12:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is completely told by the power\Nof the magnetic power then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.01,0:12:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So we are all subject to divine justice\Nwhich is absolutely perfect
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.16,0:12:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and not arbitrary or capricious\Nor vengeful.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.80,0:12:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't require all the things\Nthat have been alluded to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.80,0:12:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the source of all power.\NIt's uncertain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.83,0:12:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's poised.\NAnd it resides in the subjective.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.00,0:12:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So the quantum reality then is subjective.\NAll right, so let's skip that one
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.32,0:13:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and instead we'll go to the left-hand side of the folder.\NI think at the back we've got...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.32,0:13:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We weren't going to do quantum mechanics\Nbut if they want quantum mechanics,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.38,0:13:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,by God, they're going to get quantum mechanics.\NI don't know anything about it
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.48,0:13:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're going to hear what I know about it.\NI wanted to show this one
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.53,0:13:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because...\NWhat's the name of that guy,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.23,0:13:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the morphogenetic...\NRupert Sheldrake.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.23,0:13:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Rupert Sheldrake.\NI'm not very left-brained today.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.23,0:13:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Rupert Sheldrake's morphogenetic fields.\NYou see how the pattern within consciousness then
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.23,0:13:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,manifests in what appears to the world\Nto be a sequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.26,0:13:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the out-picturing of ABC.\NThe sequence...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.39,0:13:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This is actually just perception, see,\Nbecause you grasp first this,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.35,0:13:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,grasp this, then you grasp this.\NSo you think it's happening that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.35,0:13:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you're perceiving it that way.\NThe way it is, is ABC, like a gestalt.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.35,0:14:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It then displays itself in the world suchly.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.35,0:14:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah, we weren't going to do this one
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.20,0:14:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,because it gets us off into left brain.\NBut we'll bless left brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.75,0:14:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless left brain.\NAnd get right on in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.75,0:14:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And go right in, yeah, you know.\NSo for those that like it, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.75,0:14:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,on the internet there's a fellow named Henry Stapp.\NS-T-A-P-P.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.84,0:14:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor of Advanced Theoretical Physics at Berkeley.\NAnd his program on the internet
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.84,0:14:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is probably the best I know of\Nto make quantum mechanics
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.84,0:14:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and how it would apply to spiritual reality\Ncomprehensible to the ordinary mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.20,0:14:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We all have an ordinary mind as well as\Nan extraordinary mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.23,0:14:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, this came out in 1927.\NYou see the Schrodinger, famous Schrodinger equations.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.23,0:14:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There's two Schrodinger equations.\NOne's time dependent.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.23,0:15:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The other is time independent.\NWe don't have to go into its mathematics.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.23,0:15:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I purposely left off the mathematics.\NBut the quantum state of a system then is its potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.42,0:15:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The Heisenberg process is where choice and intention\Nand decision come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.48,0:15:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there can be no karmic responsibility,\Nno evolution if it weren't for choice and possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.55,0:15:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So intentionality.\NSo karma is set by spiritual intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.41,0:15:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of intention is what sets one's spiritual karma.\NIt's not the act but the intention behind the act.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.41,0:15:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So intentionality.\NSo Heisenberg observation, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.41,0:15:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,was on the submicroscopic level\Nthat you cannot do the same example twice
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.60,0:15:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,because having looked at it, you've already changed it\Nand it is no longer the same example.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.67,0:15:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Heisenberg process introduces choice\Nand intention and consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.67,0:16:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So consciousness enters in.\NSo the Dirac process is what happens after you observe it
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.66,0:16:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,or make a choice.\NAnd it's called the collapse of the wave function.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.66,0:16:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the universe has changed.\NIt's changed because you've looked at it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.66,0:16:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,because you've decided something.\NAnd the process by which this happens
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.69,0:16:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,was described by von Neumann as process two,\Nthe physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.69,0:16:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Process one, the mental.\NAnd as you see here, the universe can only say,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.98,0:16:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,what we said this morning,\Nthe universe, according to quantum mechanics,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.17,0:16:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,can only say yes or not yes.\NIt cannot say no.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.43,0:16:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So the kinesiologic response then\Nis explicable by quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.94,0:16:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the thing is, and if it is, your arm goes strong.\NIf it is not, your arm goes weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.00,0:16:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But it cannot say yes or no.\NIt can only say yes or not yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.00,0:16:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I ask your arm, this is the truth.\NAnd I do it by making a statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.45,0:17:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't ask a question.\NWe can say, this is an adequate description
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.52,0:17:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of what I just got through explaining.\NThis is an adequate description of choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.52,0:17:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an adequate description of choice.\NSpiritual decision and choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.16,0:17:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how we evolve spiritually.\NSo the collapse of the wave function
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.85,0:17:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,takes it from a potentiality to an actuality.\NAnd in so doing, we fulfill our karmic evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.08,0:17:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and responsibility.\NSo we can go on to the sequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.69,0:17:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,To this point of view, from this point of view,\Nof this, whatever is talking now,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.04,0:17:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it talks by itself, by the way, just like it moves by itself.\NI can't explain it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.24,0:18:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It sees this world, human world,\Nas a purgatorial realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.68,0:18:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Purgatorial in that human beings suffer.\NHuman beings have the opportunity to undo old bad karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.00,0:18:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They have the opportunity to create new karma.\NPurgatorial in that it offers the opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.32,0:18:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,from the most base and hideous of human behaviors and choices\Nto the most lofty and exquisite.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.32,0:18:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you're going to sacrifice others\Nto your personal ends,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.73,0:18:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,or sacrifice your personal ends\Nto the welfare of others out of love,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.98,0:18:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is a huge choice.\NAnd the karmic consequences are quite profound.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.98,0:18:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to evolve, then, we would have,\Nand to also be answerable for who we are,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.98,0:18:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you would have to have a universe\Nwhich is purgatorial in range of option.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.98,0:19:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If this was just heavenly,\Nand there was nothing but goodness,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.40,0:19:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and all you had was good options\Nabout good people coming from good persons,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.40,0:19:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,seeing things goodly,\Nyou're stuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.62,0:19:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, aren't you?\NYou're stuck in heaven, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.62,0:19:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NWe observed this morning that everybody is born
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.14,0:19:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,with a different calibrated level of consciousness.\NSo, therefore, life as we see it
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.27,0:19:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,within this domain is evolutionary.\NIts expression has been evolutionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.43,0:19:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And the individual consciousness is evolutionary.\NSo, you need a realm of optimal opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.43,0:19:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Optimal opportunity.\NOptimal opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.35,0:19:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We were talking today at lunch\Nabout how people get over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.35,0:20:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Viewed from that viewpoint,\Nthen, war is really a necessity, isn't it, almost, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.67,0:20:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you going to undo the karma\Nof all the people that you've killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.86,0:20:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you get killed yourself.\NOne way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.79,0:20:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you get beyond 200?\NWithin the masculine domain,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.98,0:20:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you do it by walking into a hail of bullets\Nfor the sake of the queen,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.98,0:20:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,for the sake of the throne,\Nfor the sake of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.98,0:20:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,for the sake of your country,\Nfor the sake of your comrades,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.98,0:20:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,for the sake of your regiment.\NFor something greater than yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.98,0:20:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you're willing to surrender your life.\NThat takes you above 200 forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.00,0:20:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That's in the masculine domain.\NNot to win because you're going to get the ribbon,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.80,0:20:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but because you're doing it for the university.\NYou're using it for the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.80,0:20:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Women athletes do it for womanhood.\NMen do it for whatever they may be doing it for.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.09,0:21:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they're run by testosterone.\NThe victims, there's real victimhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.32,0:21:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That testosterone loses on the planet,\Nand you got what you can see out there as history.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.99,0:21:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The way the traditional masculine way to cross over.\NYou say, why do wars keep recurring all that way?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.33,0:21:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In some ways, there's no way beyond that.\NIt's only when, for the good of the regiment,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.81,0:21:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,you walk shoulder to shoulder\Nand walk right knowingly into a hail of bullets,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.81,0:21:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're willing to die for your country,\Nyour flag, for your family, for your wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.45,0:21:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,for womanhood.\NThat's what the man does.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.22,0:21:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it for God.\NFor a higher purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.98,0:21:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You shoot above 200 forever.\NThe woman does the same thing in childbirth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.58,0:22:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of bullets, childbirth threatens her life.\NOver the centuries, she died by the millions.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.64,0:22:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The average woman died sooner or later of childbirth.\NShe had three or four children and then died.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.80,0:22:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If she got as far as three or four.\NAnd I looked through the old bible of my own family,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.89,0:22:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's the pattern.\NShe had little Ricky, she had little Jimmy,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.89,0:22:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and then she died when in childbirth.\NAnd the man at that time was on his third wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.89,0:22:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,First two had died in childbirth.\NAnd this one's pregnant, God help her.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.08,0:22:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,For the sake of bringing forth new life,\Nthe woman passes over the likelihood of death
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.56,0:22:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and faces death as a distinct possibility.\NAnd she shoots above 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.56,0:22:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The paradigm then is a little bit different.\NAll right, so the calibrated levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.98,0:22:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We went up as far as 600, I think, on that other scale.\NBecause 600, you enter a different dominion,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.98,0:23:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,a different domain.\NYou begin to transcend.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.98,0:23:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You transcend identification with the ego.\NAnd now you begin to identify as the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.49,0:23:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, you don't do anything.\NIt happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.49,0:23:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, one is blissed out.\NAnd all thought stops.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.49,0:23:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The process usually stops at that point.\NUsually stops at that point.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.55,0:23:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually stops at that point.\NUsually stops at that point.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.55,0:23:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually stops at that point.\NUsually stops at that point.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.28,0:24:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He walks and talks almost like a real human.\NHe's very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.35,0:24:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If we get over 600,\NGod help you if you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.51,0:24:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, 600 is enlightenment.\NA very profound experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.89,0:24:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Happens 1 in 10 million human lifetimes.\NExtremely profound.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.89,0:24:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,50% of the people leave.\NIt seems like luck,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.65,0:24:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,if it happens within your own experience,\Nthat somebody may come along
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.65,0:24:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and see to it that you get off the rock\Nand eat something, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.97,0:24:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Because by 700, again,\Nthe experience of Ramana Maharshi,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.04,0:24:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,for instance, is quite typical.\NAnd if you've ever been in that state,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.07,0:24:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what it is.\NHe stopped eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.16,0:24:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't talk for two years.\NThey found him in a bliss-out state.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.16,0:24:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He was covered with bugs and bugs and sores\Nand been nibbled on by mice and various things.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.36,0:25:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But he had spiritual friends who discovered him\Nand nurtured him and got him back to eating
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.61,0:25:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and various things.\NBut he did not speak for two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.61,0:25:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're into serious spiritual work\Nand meditation,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.22,0:25:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're into serious spiritual work,\Nsomebody around should know about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.76,0:25:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Your friends, your family.\NNot for the continuation of your physicality,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.82,0:25:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's irrelevant.\NWhether you topple over or not
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.82,0:25:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,is really not of any particular importance.\NBut they might haul you to a psychiatrist
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.95,0:25:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,whose decision is to find out\Nwhether you're catatonic
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.11,0:25:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and need shock treatment or not.\NRamana Maharshi would have been taken to a psychiatrist,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.17,0:25:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't he, if he was doing that today?\NSilent, not talking,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.17,0:25:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,seemed out of this world, you know?\NAnd when I was a consultant to Zen monasteries
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.72,0:26:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and I've been consulting the Catholic diocese,\NEpictetus diocese, Zen monasteries,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.72,0:26:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,all kinds of people,\Nthat was my job,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.10,0:26:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to differentiate between true spiritual states,\Nand pathologic psychiatric disorders.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.20,0:26:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this religious ecstasy?\NOr is this manic depressive psychosis
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.26,0:26:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and into religious delusions,\Nyou know, grandiose delusions?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.26,0:26:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Once in a while I get a letter\Nfrom somebody that's in that state.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.84,0:26:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,They just discovered they're God\Nand want to share the information.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.84,0:26:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I tell them, if you were God,\Nyou wouldn't be interested in sharing the information,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.84,0:26:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I'm saying?\NBut the mere fact that you asked me
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.12,0:26:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,shows that it's not likely.\NI think in chapter 10 of the last book,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.61,0:26:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,we had an audience like this.\NWe went over the attributes of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.68,0:27:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,as they really are.\NAnd we had 100% unanimity.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.51,0:27:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We divided it up into ones and twos.\NThe whole crowd of us did it
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.51,0:27:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,at Creative Life Center.\NAnd I think we listed about 18 of the qualities,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.92,0:27:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the actual qualities,\Nthe qualities of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.28,0:27:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's using the term qualities lightly.\NThe reality of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.28,0:27:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And the answers were unanimous.\NUnanimous.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.43,0:27:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you calibrate them,\Nthe energy fields of God is infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.43,0:27:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,God manifests as divinity or creator is infinite.\NThen we have other things that we have read about
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.52,0:27:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in spiritual literature.\NWithin this domain,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.07,0:27:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,within this domain,\Nthe highest calibrated level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.07,0:27:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,compatible with walking around on the planet,\Nis about a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.10,0:27:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And the reason for that appears to be\Nthat the human nervous system
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.29,0:28:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot really handle anything over a thousand.\NIt hasn't up until recent times,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.29,0:28:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,but I think it's evolving\Nthat it's going to be able to handle 1250.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.29,0:28:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But anything over 6 to 700 is already painful\Nand it feels like you're being slowly electrocuted.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.52,0:28:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha said\Nthat he felt as though his bones were broken and cracked.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.96,0:28:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He said his bones were broken and cracked.\NHe tried the same thing, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.03,0:28:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He felt as though his bones were cracked and broken.\NYes, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.67,0:28:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Christ, Buddha, Krishna, Brahman,\Nall one thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.86,0:28:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Avatar, 985.\NSelf as beyond existence or non-existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.40,0:28:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,we said at age three.\NThat was the confrontation
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.47,0:28:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,at about 850.\NReality as allness or nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.82,0:29:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Self as beyond existence or non-existence,\Nto transcend that duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.14,0:29:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,To be a teacher of enlightenment, 800.\NI as sage, 700.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.24,0:29:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Enlightenment, 600.\NBecause the other scale went up to 600
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.62,0:29:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it stopped there,\Nyou wonder what's beyond 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.88,0:29:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo that pretty much covers it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.51,0:29:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?\NWhen you said over 600, 50% leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.51,0:29:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, there, 50%.\NYou mean die?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.51,0:29:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The physicality, yes.\NYes, to leave the physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.51,0:29:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there's no interest in it.\NBy choice?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.31,0:29:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's not a realm of choice.\NThis is very hard to explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.86,0:29:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence becomes overwhelming.\NAnd one has,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.04,0:29:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,implicit and part and parcel\Nof the presence is permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.04,0:30:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a knowingness within the presence\Nthat you have permission to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.80,0:30:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be walking down the aisle\Nin the middle of a lecture
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.12,0:30:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it becomes all of a sudden\Nvery intense.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.38,0:30:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost like a magnetic attraction to leave.\NYou have complete permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.38,0:30:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a knowingness\Nthat you have permission to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.63,0:30:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know whether\Nthe physicality will continue or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.63,0:30:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It happened right during a lecture one time.\NAnd other people know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.63,0:30:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The audience didn't know\Nwhether it was going to continue
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.63,0:30:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,with the body or not either.\NIt just came out of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.88,0:30:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And the attraction to leave the body\Nwas quite intense.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.88,0:30:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And the permission was quite,\Nquite overt.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.14,0:30:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And there was no way,\Nit was, the witness watched to see
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.14,0:30:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,if the body was going to make it\Nto the end of the aisle and back or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.14,0:30:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And it did.\NSo, that's the way it went then.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.14,0:31:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It just comes out of its own.\NYou were talking about your own experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.75,0:31:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this was, yes,\Nthat was a personal experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.75,0:31:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,When it first came out,\Nit was the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.75,0:31:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,One can leave or not leave.\NAnd my presumption was
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.10,0:31:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is some karmic propensity\Nor some decision prior made
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.41,0:31:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that's running it.\NIt's not a personal decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.41,0:31:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But if some purpose is served\Nby the continuation,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.41,0:31:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,it may be that way.\NIt may go that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.41,0:31:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's no,\Nthere's no inner self
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.41,0:31:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,saying yes or no to it.\NYou know, there was only the witnessing
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.48,0:31:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of the body would continue\Nto walk down the aisle
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.48,0:31:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and make it back again\Nor it wouldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.48,0:31:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no way of knowing.\NWas that similar to 1938
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.48,0:31:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,when you were in the snow bank?\NNo, that was different.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.48,0:31:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, yes, in the same way.\NThose who've had near-death experiences,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.48,0:31:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget, there were some here, right?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.64,0:31:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There was something\Nvery characteristic about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.64,0:32:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And the difference between\Nout-of-body and near-death
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.64,0:32:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is that without a body,\Nin out-of-body there's no change
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.64,0:32:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,of calibrated level of consciousness,\Nwhich is quite surprising.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.70,0:32:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Because here you think\Nyou're a physical body.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.02,0:32:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You think your name is Dave.\NYou're laying in this bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.02,0:32:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly you're 12 feet away\Nfrom the body looking down here
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.02,0:32:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and the you is up here.\NThe you is up here
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.02,0:32:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and if thought moves\Nover this way,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.02,0:32:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the entity or whatever it is\Nmoves over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.45,0:32:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You would think after\Nsuch an experience
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.45,0:32:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that at least the realization\Nthat I'm not a physical body
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.45,0:32:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,would bring about a shift\Nof level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.45,0:32:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But surprisingly it doesn't.\NOut-of-body for some reason
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.45,0:32:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,does not bring\Na shift of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.45,0:32:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Near-death experience,\Non the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.93,0:32:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is something else.\NNear-death experience
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.06,0:32:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is much more profound.\NAnd that which was
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.06,0:33:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you think you are\Nis replaced by a presence
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.06,0:33:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of infinite love,\Nstillness, security,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.16,0:33:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that has always been.\NOne realizes
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.44,0:33:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that that's who you are.\NThat that who I am,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.18,0:33:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that which I am,\Nexisted before all universes
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.08,0:33:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and will exist after all universes\Nhave disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.27,0:33:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,After all universes\Nhave sprung forth
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.27,0:33:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,as a breath out of Indra,\Nand the dream
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.27,0:33:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,has sucked them back in,\Nthat which I am will prevail.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.27,0:33:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The certainty then\Nthat death is not a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.44,0:33:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Other people think\Nthat the death is real.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.44,0:33:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently,\Nbecause of love for them,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.57,0:33:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,there may be a decision\Nto re-breathe the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.57,0:33:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no necessity\Nto re-breathe the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.57,0:34:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And my advice is don't.\NHowever,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.73,0:34:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,if your father thinks\Nthat you've died
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.73,0:34:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,because he believes in death.\NI see my father sitting there
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.99,0:34:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and he believes in death.\NAnd if you don't re-breathe the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.15,0:34:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,he's going to think you died\Nand he's going to go through grief
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.15,0:34:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and all such.\NIt's quite apparent in that state
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.22,0:34:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that death is not a possibility.\NSo the other good news this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.60,0:34:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,or this afternoon\Nis that death is not a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.60,0:34:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not possible to die.\NThat is not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.98,0:34:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that?\NBecause of the law of conservation of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.98,0:34:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the law of conservation of energy,\Nthe law of conservation of matter,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.98,0:34:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and because that's the Newtonian paradigm,\Nthey forgot the more important paradigm,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.98,0:34:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the law of the conservation of life.\NYou cannot extinguish life.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.98,0:35:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Life can go from one form into another,\Nbut you cannot extinguish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.04,0:35:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nif a moth is flying by and you swat it,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.46,0:35:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the moth goes right on flying\Nand it's an etheric body.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.49,0:35:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't even notice the change.\NIt goes right on flying along
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.00,0:35:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's an etheric body\Nand then it comes back after a while
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.00,0:35:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,through an egg and all that\Nand comes back
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.00,0:35:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and has another physical body.\NSwat that and it doesn't even notice it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.00,0:35:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's true.\NA moth doesn't even notice it
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.19,0:35:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,if you swat it out of its physicality.\NIt doesn't even notice it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.67,0:35:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You think you killed it.\NYou didn't kill it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.80,0:35:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What a joke.\NHow could you kill it?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.80,0:35:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is the essence of existence\Nis beyond the swat,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.89,0:35:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy of life.\NYou didn't kill its electrons.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.89,0:35:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't kill anything about it,\Nbut you did knock it out of form.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.89,0:35:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you feel guilty that you've killed something\Nand you go into lifetimes of penance,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.96,0:36:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,all the things you've killed,\Nwhen you haven't killed anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.96,0:36:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If life was killable,\Nnone of us would be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.24,0:36:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This is hardly everybody in this audience's first lifetime.\NNobody gets to an audience this advanced
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.24,0:36:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in their first lifetime.\NIf life was killable,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.24,0:36:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,there would be nobody here.\NThat's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.32,0:36:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask if there are people here\Nin their first karmic lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.76,0:36:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There are.\NNobody's here in their first karmic lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.08,0:36:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no newly born spirits amongst us.\NLife is indestructible.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.30,0:36:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The law of the conservation of the energy of life,\Nfar more important than the conservation of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.36,0:37:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Life cannot be destroyed.\NYou can force it from one form into another form,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.77,0:37:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,but you cannot kill life.\NIt's not possible to kill life.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.93,0:37:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in the near-death experience,\Nthat is a realization.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.96,0:37:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's obvious that you are, before,\Nthis physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.96,0:37:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, you are before this universe.\NI was before this universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.30,0:37:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and I will still be here\Nafter this universe had disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.30,0:37:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a statement of fact.\NThat is a statement of fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.12,0:37:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It came on as a realization\Nwhen I was 12 years old in a snowbank.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.12,0:37:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,One's immortality is obvious\Nbecause the essence of the presence
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.43,0:37:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,of the source of your own existence\Nis what you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.43,0:37:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So, how could you be separated\Nfrom your own essence
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.52,0:38:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which you are?\NNot possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.74,0:38:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So, after a near-death experience,\Nthere's a curious loss of fear of death,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.74,0:38:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,which I didn't know about\Nuntil a few years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.93,0:38:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But, experientially,\Nall fear of death disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.93,0:38:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in World War II,\Nwhen people were blowing up
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.06,0:38:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and people were throwing up with fear, etc.,\Nthere wasn't the slightest even concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.06,0:38:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, there'd be a mind\Nready to go off right next to the ship
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.06,0:38:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and the horns of this mind\Nwould be bumping against them.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.06,0:38:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody would swat with fear.\NAnd I'd fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.06,0:38:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,look, keep that guy away from me.\NIt was only concerned with the job
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.06,0:38:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of keeping that thing from bumping us.\NThe fact that you could blow up
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.06,0:38:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,never even crossed my mind.\NSo, there was a peculiar loss of fear of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.35,0:38:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Death has lost its possibility as a reality.\NAnd therefore, an oncoming bullet or something
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.35,0:38:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't bother you at all.\NYou just don't want the shooter
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.35,0:38:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to feel guilty that he killed you\Nbecause, you know, it's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.35,0:39:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,As I say,\Nyou're enlightened
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.35,0:39:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and somebody's going to assassinate you,\Nwhat do you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.35,0:39:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You go,\NI hate loud noses, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.35,0:39:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate loud noises.\NHe's doing what he thinks he's got to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.48,0:39:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, God bless him.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.48,0:39:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,if he does it for a holler or whatever.\NAll right, so,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.48,0:39:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that takes care of near death.\NNear death experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.50,0:39:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Transformative.\NAnd the calibrated level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.50,0:39:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,before and after a near death experience\Nis quite remarkable.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.50,0:39:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course,\Nmany people have remarked about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.50,0:39:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctors have written about it.\NPeople who survive heart attacks
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.50,0:39:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,will tell you their life is transformed.\NAll the materialistic goals they had before
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.50,0:39:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,now seem ridiculous.\NThe love of,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.85,0:39:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,love then becomes the predominant motif.\NMost people,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.65,0:39:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,gone through double,\Ntriple bypass
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.65,0:40:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and near death of cardiac arrest,\Nusually are quite a bit different
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.36,0:40:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,when they survive.\NUnless they're imbeciles.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.96,0:40:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody here trans,\Nsurvived cardiac arrest
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.96,0:40:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,or major cardiac events?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.09,0:40:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a pretty young audience.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.09,0:40:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But any of those who have\Nknow that life is profoundly different.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.09,0:40:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, okay.\NWe're trying to transcend the mind then.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.47,0:40:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,If the mind is the big block,\Nand then a group like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.47,0:40:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,which calibrates at 435,\Nin a group like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.47,0:40:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind is the ultimate block.\NYou've got the spiritual motivation,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.47,0:40:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got the know-how,\Nyou've got all the books,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.47,0:40:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the teachers, etc.\NSo, the thing that intervenes then
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.47,0:40:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is thinkingness itself.\NAnd the problem then
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.47,0:40:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is how to transcend\Nthe identification with the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.47,0:40:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,For a group like this,\Nwhich is pretty sophisticated,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.40,0:40:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we already know we're not the,\Nwe know we're not the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.40,0:41:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That we're pretty certain about.\NI mean, if you take off your arm,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.40,0:41:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you're still you.\NIf you take off this arm,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.40,0:41:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you're still you.\NIf you take off this leg,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.40,0:41:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you're still you.\NIf you take off this leg,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.40,0:41:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you're still you.\NYou take off an ear,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.40,0:41:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you take off a thumb,\Nno matter what you take off,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.40,0:41:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you still say I.\NSo, you get,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.40,0:41:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't be the physical body,\Nor I'd only feel like half my eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.40,0:41:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,half an eye.\NYou know?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.40,0:41:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If my thumb went to heaven,\NI'd say,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.40,0:41:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,well, I'm less of an eye\Nthan I used to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.40,0:41:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?\NHe's waiting for me over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.40,0:41:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me back my thumb, God.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.75,0:41:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care of that karma.\NAnyway, I'm sorry
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.75,0:41:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I stuck my thumb in your eye,\NMiss Kelly.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.75,0:41:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, all right.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.12,0:41:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo, when you,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.12,0:41:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,in contemplation and meditation then,\Nyou'll notice that there are fields
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.12,0:41:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and levels of awareness.\NAt first, you're aware of form.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.22,0:41:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's content.\NThis is the ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.22,0:41:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,structure and form.\NThis is what people complain about
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.22,0:42:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,when they go to try meditating.\NI can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.22,0:42:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't get my mind to stop\Ncreating pictures, images, memories
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.22,0:42:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and all that whole tantasmagoria.\NIf you watch the rise and fall
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.72,0:42:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of the content of consciousness,\Npretty soon you become aware
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.72,0:42:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're not the content\Nbecause the content is constantly flowing by
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.72,0:42:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,like a river.\NAnd instead, what you are
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.72,0:42:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,is the witness, the watcher.\NAnd so, identification is not
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.91,0:42:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,with the content of consciousness now,\Nbut the witness,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.10,0:42:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the witness and the recognizing\Nor the observer.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.92,0:42:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You become that\Nwhich is witnessing the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.92,0:42:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, instead of identifying\Nwith the content of the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.92,0:42:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you become aware\Nthat you are the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.92,0:42:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You are the witness,\Nthe watcher,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.92,0:42:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the experiencer,\Nthe observer.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.00,0:43:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Gadatta Maharaj\Nbecame enlightened
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.36,0:43:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,after only not too many years.\NAnd the teaching of his guru
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.87,0:43:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,was to watch the mind.\NAnd Mr. Gadatta,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.22,0:43:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,who calibrated about 720 or so,\Nthe same as Ramana Maharshi,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.22,0:43:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,taught people to really watch the mind.\NSo, what he was saying was
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.91,0:43:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,focus on,\Nfocus up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.04,0:43:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't focus on content of mind,\Nfocus the watcher,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.04,0:43:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the watcher, the witness of mind.\NThen you begin to realize
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.13,0:43:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that watching and witnessing\Nis happening of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.13,0:43:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not deciding to witness and watch\Nwhat goes on in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.13,0:43:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an impersonal phenomenon.\NSo, if you identify with the content of mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.00,0:43:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you think it's personal.\NThen you realize,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.00,0:43:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,how could it be personal?\NBecause you don't have any choice
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.00,0:44:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,whether to witness and watch\Nwhat's going on in the content of mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.00,0:44:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's happening of its own.\NYou can't take credit for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.25,0:44:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither should you take this credit.\NSo, one quality,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.25,0:44:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,now you begin to notice\Nthe impersonal qualities of mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.25,0:44:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It automatically witnesses and watches\Nand automatically registers
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.25,0:44:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,because it is a phenomenon coming out\Nof a quality of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.25,0:44:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The unmanifest,\Nthe unmanifest,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.12,0:44:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the unmanifest becomes the manifest.\NThe unmanifest is the Godhead,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.82,0:44:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes manifest as divinity,\Nthe allness of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.82,0:44:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,All that is created,\Nboth visible and invisible,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.30,0:44:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,comes out of the unmanifest,\Nbecoming manifest,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.30,0:44:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,radiates out as the light of consciousness,\Nwhich is the source of all life.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.20,0:44:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently,\Nthe reason you can't kill life
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.20,0:45:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is because you can't kill God.\NThe thought that you could kill life
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.80,0:45:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,would mean that you could kill a part of God.\NNot possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.85,0:45:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we can stop feeling guilty\Nabout all the little ants we stepped on.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.85,0:45:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, there's a certain point\Nin spiritual evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.85,0:45:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,where you feel guilty about every ant\Nthat you might have stepped on.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.85,0:45:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It is some sort of a semi-Buddhist tradition\Nthat religion,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.98,0:45:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,they wear mosquito nettings\Nso they won't breathe any bacteria in their mosquitoes
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.98,0:45:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and accidentally kill them.\NThey must be doing some karma there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.46,0:45:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go on next.\NFrom carelessness about life,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.46,0:45:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,now one becomes overly protective about it.\NOkay?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.26,0:45:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the next one?\NIs that the next one?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.51,0:45:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't believe it's the next one.\NLet me see on the list.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.51,0:46:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me see the list on there.\NIt seems to me we're missing something
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.92,0:46:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we wanted to explain.\NWe'll explain it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.92,0:46:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't need a picture anyway.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.56,0:46:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me just see the list,\Nthe typed list.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.56,0:46:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There you go.\NThere it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.56,0:46:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to make sure\Nall the ones I brought.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.63,0:46:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yes, we did, didn't we?\NOkay, let's just go through
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.82,0:46:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the application of calibrated levels of consciousness\Nto the world that we look at.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.82,0:46:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.\NThe calibrated levels of consciousness, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.06,0:46:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,are a profound implication.\NWe mentioned this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.25,0:46:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the application of spiritual principles in business.\NWe gave Walmart as an example,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.60,0:46:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrating at around 350,\Nof integrity in business.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.60,0:46:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Integrity in business is not airy-fairy.\NIt shows up on the bottom line
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.80,0:46:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,as the biggest corporation\Nand most successful corporation in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.12,0:46:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo this is application of business.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.12,0:47:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We've done a lot of research\Ncalibrating the levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.12,0:47:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the world of spirituality\Nover great periods of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.12,0:47:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Gitas,\Nwhere they calibrate ancient Hindu Vedas
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.12,0:47:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in the 900s,\Nall the way down to current writers, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.15,0:47:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,One application that we ran across\Nbecause of the 9-11 and the recent events
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.15,0:47:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,was to calibrate the regions of the world.\NSo people are following
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.34,0:47:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and demonstrating karmic patterns.\NIt's like great cycles of people
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.34,0:47:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,who come in and come in together.\NWe see North America.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.40,0:47:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What did we say our group was here today?\N435, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.40,0:47:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, this group is 435.\NYou see, the higher you go,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.63,0:47:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the more high it is\Nbecause you're talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.63,0:47:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,logarithmic progression.\NSo 400 is not twice 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.88,0:48:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's immensely more than 200\Nbecause it's the log of 400.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.01,0:48:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so 421 is America today.\N415, 410 is North America.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.17,0:48:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, Mexico is 255.\NLet's see if that's still so.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.17,0:48:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to me it should be higher than that.\NMexico is over 255, 260.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.17,0:48:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's still 255. Okay.\NAll right, then we go into the Caribbean islands.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.24,0:48:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We go into middle America.\NWe see that it's in the 300s.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.13,0:48:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So throughout...\NSo in the high 400s,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.64,0:48:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you go on down and you're in the 300s.\NThe 300s are still extremely high.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.64,0:48:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,300s are a very high energy.\NThat's a lot of ambition,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.77,0:48:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of integrity,\Na lot of willingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.77,0:48:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see that this hemisphere, then,\Nis potentially a pretty peaceful place.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.77,0:48:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got 400s and you've got 300s.\NAnd then suddenly in the middle of all this,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.77,0:49:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,if you calibrate all these maps,\Nyour Central America 305,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.77,0:49:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly you see a 55.\NYeah, turns out to be Haiti.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.02,0:49:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, okay.\NSo, you see, consciousness research,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.02,0:49:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't take any position by it.\NYou say, if we use this research
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.02,0:49:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and we begin examining nature, animals,\Ngeography, populace, civilization,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.02,0:49:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, what kind of a picture will emerge?\NSo we find that here is a whole hemisphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.24,0:49:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,extremely high calorific,\Nhigh calibration,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.24,0:49:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and right in the middle of it you have 55.\NSo you just put this in your noodle
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.37,0:49:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand the events of history,\Nthe events of political realities
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.63,0:49:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and what the implication is.\NWhat is the implication of 55
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.63,0:49:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in the middle of 300s and 400s?\NWe know that sending,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.76,0:49:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it was tried to send money there\Nand it made things worse
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.76,0:50:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because it increased nutrition,\Nit created population growth,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.76,0:50:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and the poverty got worse.\NSo the question is then,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.76,0:50:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you do with a country that calibrates at 55?\NYou see, it's a completely different question.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.76,0:50:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so let's go to the next one.\NCalibration of 9-11?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.58,0:50:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think so, no.\NIt takes a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.58,0:50:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the level of consciousness of mankind,\Nno single event changes it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.58,0:50:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,9-11 doesn't change it.\NWorld War II doesn't change it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.58,0:50:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It stayed at 190 after many centuries.\NDuring those centuries,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.58,0:50:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you had the Black Plague,\Nyou had the, what was it,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.77,0:50:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the Church of the Churches,\Nthe Inquisition,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.77,0:50:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you had World War I,\Nyou had the Napoleonic Wars,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.77,0:50:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,you had mass starvation,\Nyou had the great pneumonia,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.70,0:51:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,encephalitis, epidemics after World War I.\NAnd none of those things changed
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.02,0:51:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the level of consciousness of mankind.\NNow we see a more complicated picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.18,0:51:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What we did with one side of the hemisphere,\Nis this the right sequence?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.18,0:51:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.18,0:51:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so now if we do this\Nand calibrate all the levels
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.18,0:51:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of all the countries in the world,\Nwhat do we find out?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.18,0:51:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we see Australia, 410.\NWe see Malaysia, 405.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.18,0:51:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We see India, 355.\NWe see China, 305.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.18,0:51:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We see Japan and Korea.\NKorea's about 425 or 430.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.28,0:51:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We see Mongolia, 175.\NSo what can we learn from this?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.28,0:51:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the inference, of course, is quite profound.\NJust merely looking it over,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.14,0:51:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you certainly get a different feeling\Nfor life on this planet
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.14,0:51:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and how it's distributed,\Nwhat to expect.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.14,0:52:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The implications for peace is profound\Nbecause the implications for government,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.00,0:52:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,politics and economics is profound.\NBecause most countries seem to be completely insensitive
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.96,0:52:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to what is the consciousness level\Nof the people they are talking to.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.96,0:52:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you expressing anything in a language\Nthat is even comprehensible or meaningful?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.96,0:52:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You talk about democracy and freedom\Nto people who calibrate at 50,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.47,0:52:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,they're worrying about whether or not\Nthey're going to survive till tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.60,0:52:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,if they don't have enough food.\NForget about voting for somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.60,0:52:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,They're going to vote for whoever gives them food,\Nthat's how the drug dealer gains power
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.66,0:52:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,over the neighborhood\Nbecause he becomes the Don.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.66,0:52:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,In Chicago, that was historic, wasn't it?\NSo the gangster becomes the hero
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.95,0:53:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're all starving\Nand he passes out the jobs and the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.95,0:53:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's who you vote for.\NYou vote for somebody that's going to keep you
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.95,0:53:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and your children alive.\NSo now you see the implications
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.36,0:53:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,for diplomacy, for understanding.\NSo if you look at each level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.26,0:53:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you go back to the map of consciousness,\Nyou begin to understand human history
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.26,0:53:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in a completely different way\Nthan you've ever understood it before.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.52,0:53:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the problems in the world right now\Nare coming from North Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.52,0:53:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What are those two countries that are always at it?\NIsrael and Palestine, where are they up there?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.64,0:53:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They're about 180, 180 to 190.\NWhen people say, I want peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.12,0:53:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and you calibrate there at 180,\Nyou know they're lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.56,0:53:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Because their whole shtick comes out of war, right?\NI kill you, then you kill me, then I kill you,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.56,0:53:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,then I throw a rocket at you,\Nthen I put the fire hose on you, then I bomb you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.56,0:54:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, that's their whole life.\NYou get a gun, you're somebody,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.01,0:54:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you get on TV,\Npeace is political.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.58,0:54:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't mean peace at all.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.68,0:54:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if you want peace, you have peace.\NIf you actually want peace, you have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.25,0:54:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't have it,\Nit's because you don't really want it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.48,0:54:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You're just using it as a political slogan\Nto get votes and justify your political maneuvering.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.64,0:54:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the other thing that calibrating these things does\Nis unveil the liars in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.64,0:54:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why these lectures are not necessarily popular\Nin that part of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.67,0:54:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,When the people think it's the walking god\Nand you calibrate his 180,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.67,0:54:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,can we come down anymore?\NOkay, I just wanted to get Africa
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.67,0:54:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,where I can put my fingers on it.\NHere we have Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.67,0:54:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, as low as 50, as low as 40.\N40.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.56,0:55:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's practically a walking death.\NHow they stay alive at 40 is a mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.56,0:55:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,70, 40.\NHere you have ongoing civil wars for decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.56,0:55:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't just conquer each other,\Nthey slaughter each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.56,0:55:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,When this tribe takes this one over,\Nthey kill them all and chop them in small pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.56,0:55:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't just kill them.\NThey massacre them.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.82,0:55:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So here you see brutality, starvation.\NYou see AIDS ravaging the populace.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.11,0:55:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And you look up at Europe,\Nyou see the 400s, the high 300s.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.00,0:55:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You look at Scandinavia.\NHere's Spain, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.00,0:55:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,France, all these various countries.\NAnd you begin to see the implications for mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.20,0:55:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The implications for mankind.\NWhat kind of attention has to be put where?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.36,0:55:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,How to phrase that?\NWhat is meaningful to people?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.66,0:56:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The holier-than-thou attitude of our government,\Nwhich antagonizes a good part of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.66,0:56:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,How should you address the president\Nof the largest country in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.01,0:56:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that has a culture 6,000 years old,\Nthat was civilized for 6,000 years
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.24,0:56:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,before your country was even heard of?\NHow should one address such a person?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.40,0:56:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I would say with respect.\NWith respect, you might get a positive response.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.81,0:56:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,With a superior attitude,\Nyou get non-cooperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.52,0:56:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So the implications for international peace,\Nsuccess, and diplomacy
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.52,0:56:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of understanding the calibrated levels of consciousness\Nof various peoples,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.52,0:56:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the country, the government,\Nand the ruling regime
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.52,0:56:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is quite profound.\NIt makes the difference between life and death.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.06,0:56:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There are not no such things\Nas we are talking about this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.06,0:56:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Mankind was ignorant.\NYou see?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.28,0:57:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The bottom of the ocean is covered\Nwith the skeletons of the dead sailors
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.28,0:57:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of the centuries.\NThe bottom of the oceans are covered
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.83,0:57:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,with the wreckage of thousands\Nand thousands of ships
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.83,0:57:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,because they had no compass.\NNo compass.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.57,0:57:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No compass.\NThe cost in lives was enormous.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.57,0:57:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The bottom of the sea\Nwas covered with ships
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.57,0:57:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and the bodies of brave people\Nwho had no compass.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.64,0:57:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we have a compass.\NSo we can no longer claim ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.86,0:57:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No longer claim ignorance.\NHere's an easier definition
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.18,0:57:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,which is quick to see.\NAnd again, we see.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.31,0:57:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,These all seem to be safe areas\Nwhere you can address people
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.31,0:57:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,from the viewpoint.\NSee, the world of the intellect
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.82,0:57:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is for the 400s.\NThat's reason and logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.88,0:58:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,To address people on a different\Nconsciousness level with reason and logic,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.88,0:58:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you sound stupid.\NYou sound stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.95,0:58:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so here you've got,\Nlet me see the world again.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.17,0:58:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I just,\Nit's such an easy thing to hold in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.17,0:58:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but it changes your whole understanding\Nof the daily newspaper, of history,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.17,0:58:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of history as recounted by\Nthe political history
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.17,0:58:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and what has gone on\Nover the centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.17,0:58:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And we just came back\Nfrom two weeks in Europe
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.17,0:58:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,where we talked at Oxford University\Nand we got to see,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.65,0:58:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,it was like a rerun of history\Nfrom the 1400s, 1500s.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.16,0:58:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's like a confront\Nwith human history
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.16,0:58:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the Middle Ages\Nup until the present time.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.39,0:58:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The architecture,\Nthe lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.39,0:58:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and ambiance of the people\Nis frozen throughout all time
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.39,0:59:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in its sculpture, in its art,\Nin its artistry.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.68,0:59:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Incredibly impressive.\NSo let's go on to the next one again
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.96,0:59:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we'll look at the other side of the world.\NAnd I don't know what happens
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.19,0:59:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,after the other side of the world.\NOh yeah, the application.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.92,0:59:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,See what a profound importance\Nin consciousness research is
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.92,0:59:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,because you discover things\Nthat nobody's ever known.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.92,0:59:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody in the State Department\Nknows anything about what we're talking about today.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.84,0:59:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody.\NNot the most brilliant and experienced heads of government
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.84,0:59:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,know what we all know this instant.\NWe have already surpassed all governments
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.84,0:59:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and diplomats\Nthroughout all of human history.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.84,0:59:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We now know more at one glance\Nthan they've ever been able to discover
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.84,0:59:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all of time.\NThat's the payoff of consciousness research.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.84,0:59:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So now,\Nwe look at the great regions of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.84,0:59:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you bring it down a little bit?\NHere's South Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.84,0:59:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's Madagascar.\NHere's the very dark parts of Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.84,1:00:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the dark parts of Africa.\NHere you see
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.84,1:00:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,North Africa,\Nthe Near East, the Middle East
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.84,1:00:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,where all the trouble is constantly going on.\NWhere you're going to have trouble is
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.84,1:00:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in countries that calibrate 180 to 190\Nbecause they're prideful,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.84,1:00:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,they're into revenge,\Nthey're into mutual hatred,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.97,1:00:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're into\Nlying, frankly.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.07,1:00:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Not telling the truth.\NIf they were telling the truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.07,1:00:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,they would calibrate over 200.\NSo what's fun is to watch the evening news
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.07,1:00:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and watch these world leaders come on\Nand calibrate.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.07,1:00:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He gives this big thing, you know?\NYou say, what's the level of truth
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.07,1:00:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of that lecture that he just gave?\N180.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.38,1:00:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We've had world-renowned figures and calibrated them\Nand the entire address
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.38,1:00:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to the world\Nwas one lie from the end.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.89,1:00:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, is there any truth in anything he said\Nin the last half hour?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.89,1:01:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, no.\NTo convincingly lie for half an hour
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.28,1:01:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,non-stop.\NBut that's a job requirement.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.85,1:01:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We say Australia should be doing\Nextremely well.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.85,1:01:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It is in any way.\NYou see the trouble spots of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.85,1:01:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You can tailor your expectations then.\NIf you sign a contract,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.23,1:01:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it's only going to be valid\Nif the other person
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.23,1:01:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,holds the same values\Nas you do.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.23,1:01:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,If they don't hold the same values,\Nthey think you're stupid.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.74,1:01:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll move on to the next one.\NWe want to see
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.96,1:01:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the applications of consciousness research\Nin many areas of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.96,1:01:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This is how we do it.\NAs you can see,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.51,1:01:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not exactly ready for publication.\NIt's all done in pencil.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.51,1:01:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But it took a number of weekends to do all this\Nand great patience, I'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.51,1:02:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Over on the upper right hand,\Nwe can pull them down.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.64,1:02:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Somewhere we have this typed up.\NThis particular one, we didn't get around to typing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.18,1:02:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The trouble spots of the world.\NWe should really try to define
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.18,1:02:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the problem with these people.\NYou see?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.18,1:02:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And you get their 185, their 165,\Ntheir 175, their 160,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.18,1:02:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,180, 185,\N190, 180,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.18,1:02:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,all less than 200.\NUnless you get the turkey,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.66,1:02:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,70 turkeys is over 200, 245.\NSo you see,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.66,1:02:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,we can tailor our expectation\Nof international relationships,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.66,1:02:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,diplomacy,\Nour political ideology,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.76,1:02:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to the reality of who these people really are\Nand how they see life.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.76,1:02:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, the next one.\NHow they see life.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.96,1:02:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The world in which I grew up\Nsaw life in a certain way.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.96,1:03:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The world in which we live now\Nsees life in a different way.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.31,1:03:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's the implications\Nfor human survival?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.27,1:03:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want to show you the practical results\Nof consciousness research.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.27,1:03:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It completely\Nstrips illusion
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.27,1:03:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and lays bare\Nthe bonds of reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.07,1:03:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you will not find reality and truth\Nin the daily newspaper,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.45,1:03:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll find distortions.\NAlright, so let's look at World War II.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.52,1:03:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,To begin with,\Npeace is not something you cause
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.93,1:03:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,or create,\Nit's that which you become.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.32,1:03:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace is the automatic consequence\Nof truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.08,1:03:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Where truth prevails,\Npeace is automatic.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.08,1:03:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,War is the automatic consequence\Nof falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.18,1:03:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So the way to peace then\Nis by insisting on
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.34,1:03:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the prevalence of truth.\NIntegrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.34,1:04:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So the way to peace then\Nis through integrity,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.34,1:04:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the dedication and devotion\Nto God's truth and peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.92,1:04:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So can you bring it down just a little bit?\NSo peace is the natural state
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.92,1:04:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,where truth prevails.\NWar is the automatic state
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.92,1:04:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,when falsehood prevails.\NTherefore, the basis of war
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.92,1:04:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is ignorance.\NMankind has had no basis
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.17,1:04:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to tell truth from falsehood,\Nso he's not faulted for ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.17,1:04:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, Jesus Christ\Nas well as the Buddha
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.91,1:04:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,said there's only one sin\Nand that is ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.91,1:04:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Man had no compass to go by,\Nso how answerable is he?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.91,1:04:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The basis of war, therefore,\Nis not evil and awfulness
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.93,1:04:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,but stupidity and ignorance.\NWhy is that so?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.93,1:04:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the human mind\Ncannot discern truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.08,1:04:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The importance of the discovery\Nof a test to discern truth from falsehood
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.08,1:05:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the human mind\Nis intrinsically designed
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.08,1:05:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and incapable of telling truth from falsehood.\NIt's convincible.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.10,1:05:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You can argue with it.\NYou can persuade it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.10,1:05:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But the mind in and of itself\Nis like the hardware of a computer.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.32,1:05:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So the ego,\Nall the belief systems
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.32,1:05:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,are the software.\NYou can see that the hardware
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.32,1:05:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of a computer is innocent.\NYou can run any software through it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.32,1:05:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The hardware remains unsullied.\NSo the ego is the software,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.58,1:05:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness is the hardware,\Nand the human mind
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.74,1:05:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot discern truth from falsehood.\NSo real spiritual progress
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.96,1:05:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is always based on humility.\NThe first,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.09,1:05:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,most profound humility\Nis the acceptance
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.09,1:05:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that the human mind\Nin and of itself
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.09,1:06:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,is unable to tell truth from falsehood.\NUnable to tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.05,1:06:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The human mind can be\Nbrainwashed into believing anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.82,1:06:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Joseph Gables\Nwas an expert.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.82,1:06:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He could convince you\Nthat black was white.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.82,1:06:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He just kept saying it over.\NIf a lie is repeated often enough,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.82,1:06:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the human mind will believe it.\NSo we as leaders
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.92,1:06:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of spiritual truth\Nhave to become aware
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.04,1:06:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that our first humility\Nis, oh Lord,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.04,1:06:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in and of itself\Nand I cannot tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.84,1:06:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Human mind cannot discern\Ntruth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.54,1:06:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequence is\Nthe inability to discern
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.54,1:06:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,a leader from a megalomaniac.\NSo the history of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.67,1:06:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is in the last century\N100 million human beings
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.70,1:06:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,have been slaughtered\Nby megalomaniacs.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.70,1:07:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,How astonishing.\N100 million people have died
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.79,1:07:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,because they can't tell\Na megalomaniac from a leader.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.20,1:07:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be like 100 million people\Ndying of poison apples
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.16,1:07:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,because they can't discern\Na poison apple from a regular apple.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.16,1:07:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't you think a human being\Nwould know that by now?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.16,1:07:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If you watched generation after generation\Nand hundreds of millions of people die,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.84,1:07:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,people would begin to say\Nhow can we tell a leader from a maniac?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.48,1:07:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Inability to discern a leader\Nfrom a megalomaniac.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.82,1:07:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is,\Nthe ego gets easily,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.82,1:07:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,because of its ignorance,\Npolarized into ego positions,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.82,1:07:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,distortion of truth and propaganda.\NThe cost to mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.64,1:07:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is death and destruction.\NLet's just say,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.64,1:08:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,if we have now something\Nthat reveals the absolute truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.64,1:08:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,what if we go back over history\Nand examine something,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.64,1:08:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I just picked this one\Nand I knew all the people.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.84,1:08:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we look\Nand we see,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.84,1:08:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,how do all these people calibrate?\NWe can look at the Normandy,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.84,1:08:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,we can look at all the details\Nof World War II
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.84,1:08:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,with which we're all familiar.\NWe can look at the military
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.03,1:08:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,at Pearl Harbor,\Nwe can look at kamikaze pilots
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.03,1:08:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,at the lunch hour.\NWhat about a kamikaze pilot?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.03,1:08:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I always see him\Nas a brave person
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.92,1:08:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,committed to serving\Nhis emperor and his country
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.92,1:08:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and the sun god,\Nand therefore a noble.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.92,1:08:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,After World War II,\Nall the former enemies
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.12,1:08:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,forgave each other\Nand we all gave recognition
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.50,1:08:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to the warrior,\Nthe nobility of the warrior.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.79,1:09:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We may have been mistaken,\Nbut we may have been mistaken,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.79,1:09:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but our motive was to serve\Ngod, country, and family.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.79,1:09:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So a kamikaze pilot,\Nwe see Adolf Hitler,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.79,1:09:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,345.\NEmperor Hirohito
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.79,1:09:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,was right on the edge.\NTojo was a little better.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.79,1:09:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto, surprisingly,\Nwas 205.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.13,1:09:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So these were people\Nwho were patriotic,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.13,1:09:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,dedicated to their country,\Nthey believed in their cause.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.03,1:09:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200,\Nwe see Adolf Hitler,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.03,1:09:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,45 at the time of his death.\NI think Joseph Stalin,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.03,1:09:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,was a wishy-washy guy.\NAnd when Neville Chamberlain
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.03,1:09:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,went to Hitler and got him\Nto sign a peace treaty,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.03,1:09:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,he went home a big hero.\NPeace in our time.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.03,1:09:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And Hitler thought he was an idiot.\NHitler thought Neville Chamberlain
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.41,1:10:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,was really a dumbbell.\NThat is a fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.37,1:10:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitler thought, what an idiot.\NChamberlain walked out,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.37,1:10:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,he went home a hero.\NSo he called up the troops,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.37,1:10:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,no opposition now,\Nand so you can see
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.50,1:10:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,what went on with\Nthe League of Nations,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.92,1:10:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,did nothing really to stop it.\NThey could have stopped it very easily
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.92,1:10:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in the beginning.\NThe attack on Pearl Harbor,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.92,1:10:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the London Blitz,\Nthe Cambridge Five,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.17,1:10:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,we see treason,\NLord Ha Ha,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.27,1:10:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,traitors,\NTokyo Rose,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.27,1:10:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. McGonagall.\NYou see,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.33,1:10:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,we're consciousness scientists\Nthis afternoon,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.33,1:10:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,we're talking about\Nhow can you objectively
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.91,1:10:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,re-examine spiritual truth.\NA lot of the work I've done
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.91,1:11:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,has to do with\Nthe verification of spiritual realities.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.92,1:11:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, well you see\Nthere were the traitors
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.92,1:11:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,out of that,\Nthe Cambridge Five,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.92,1:11:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Nwho gave the nuclear secrets
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.92,1:11:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to other countries,\Nhowever they rationalized it,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.92,1:11:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,they did,\Nand they crashed.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.08,1:11:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do with the Iraqi War\Nbecause it's very recent
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.24,1:11:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in people's mind,\Nand it may not be
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.24,1:11:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in accord with your belief system,\Nfor which I apologize,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.24,1:11:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but the way to God, nobody said it was easy.\NI'll explain
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.24,1:11:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,President Bush\Nso that you don't have to say,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.24,1:11:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,what about President Bush?\NPresident Bush,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.50,1:11:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I know his consciousness,\Nhe took an oath,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.50,1:12:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,in fact he told you,\NI took an oath as President of the United States
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.56,1:12:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to defend this country against all enemies,\Nand that is his prime commitment.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.56,1:12:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So when he puts his hand on a Bible,\Nhe's a man who himself has evolved
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.56,1:12:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,because of spiritual convictions,\Nwhen he puts his hand on a Bible
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.56,1:12:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that he will do that,\Nyou know he will do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.56,1:12:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now how he does that,\Nyou may not agree with,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.56,1:12:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,but his intention is at 460,\Nso these people are all coming from about 450 or 460.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.56,1:12:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The U.S. Congress,\Neverybody in the U.S. population,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.72,1:12:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the intention,\Nthe intention was to,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.72,1:12:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,was integrity.\NBelow 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.72,1:12:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we see the position of other\Npeople at the time
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.92,1:12:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of the\N9-11,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.92,1:12:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to say,\Nwe're rerunning what happened at 9-11,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.92,1:12:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you see Saddam Hussein,\Nyou see Jihad,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.92,1:12:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Jihad is very dangerous,\Nyou see Jihad at 50,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.98,1:13:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you better be scared of it,\NJihad is real,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.04,1:13:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's really,\Nthey'll explode or bomb anything,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.04,1:13:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and the most dangerous person on the planet\Nis a religious zealot,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.04,1:13:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,a religious zealot is the most dangerous thing going,\Nit's like an atomic bomb on the loose,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.04,1:13:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean,\NNorth Korea,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.28,1:13:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't do North Korea recently,\Nwe did North Korea,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.28,1:13:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,we were in Korea,\Ntrying to resolve the conflict,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.28,1:13:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,at that time we were successful in 1999 I think,\Nat the time I think,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.69,1:13:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,let's just,\Ndo you want to do them,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.69,1:13:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if we have permission?\NLet's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.30,1:13:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to do the Koreas now\Nin front of this audience,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.98,1:13:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,resist.\NI thought I'd show it to you because you can see the practicality
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.66,1:14:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of the application of consciousness research in\Nthe everyday world and then the spiritual implications
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.90,1:14:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,of this work as it reveals itself.\NOne more. What did you sing?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.44,1:14:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's coming out in a book that we're working on. Here we again\NWar and Peace. This is how we run quickly through a bunch of wars
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.10,1:14:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can see the usefulness. The Korean War, you see\Nwhere everybody was there. North Korea at that time was 80.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.08,1:14:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The communist regime was at 90. The U.S. position was\N300. South Korea was 300. All those things have shifted since
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.18,1:14:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but at the time. At the time of the Korean War, this is how\Nthings lined up. At the time of the Cold War
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.44,1:14:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you find out some interesting things.\NPeople accused the Vietnam War
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.88,1:15:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,veterans of faking it and all the Vietnam Syndrome, etc.\NWe ask, was PTSD an actual clinical fact?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.88,1:15:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We get, yes, it is an actual clinical fact. We know many\Npeople blown out by the Vietnam War who never recovered.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.91,1:15:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We see what the positions of everyone\Nwas at the time. Not too admirable on a
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.01,1:15:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,wide-scale viewpoint. During the Cold War, we see what the\Npositions were. That was quite a few years, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.42,1:15:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither side comes out particularly\Nbrilliantly. Neither the CIA, U.S. Intelligence,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.42,1:15:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,nor the Russian KGB.\NNone of them come out to be very sterling kind of institutions.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.78,1:15:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Khrushchev and Brezhnev, etc.\NWhat went on in the Gulf War? We see President Bush, that was the elder,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.81,1:16:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,at 400, U.S. Military at 310.\NAgain we ask, Gulf War Syndrome, is that a fact or is that something
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.81,1:16:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,they just made up? The answer we got was that it was an actual\Nfact. Saddam Hussein calibrated at 95.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.10,1:16:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Kuwait at the time was 195.\NWorld War I, what went on? President Woodrow Wilson was 400.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.19,1:16:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And again we ask, was shell shock an actual clinical\Nfact? And the answer we get is yes. So the devastation
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.19,1:16:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of war on individual soldier is real. The Gulf War Syndrome,\NVietnam War Syndrome, shell shock after
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.19,1:16:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,World War I are actual facts. It's a fact.\NIn World War I, President Wilson was 400 and Kaiser Wilhelm
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.99,1:16:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,was at 165. We thought for fun we'd go\Nback to the Battle of Waterloo. And the
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.34,1:17:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Battle of Waterloo, the Duke of Wellington was 405\Nand Napoleon was 75.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.70,1:17:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're going to put your money out there, it would be nice to know these, right?\NPut your money on the Duke of Wellington.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.70,1:17:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Put your money on the Duke of Wellington.\NSo we invest then our energies and our efforts
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.70,1:17:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in line with that which is integrous.\NWith that which is integrous. Definably and verifiably
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.73,1:17:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,integrous. Why? Because we say to\Nourselves, my own mind in and of itself is unable
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.89,1:17:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to discern truth from falsehood as clever as I think I am.\NEverybody's mind thinks it's quite clever.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.86,1:17:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody here who doesn't think his own mind is clever?\NWhatever your mind is. It was so clever nobody
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.39,1:18:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,answered, right?\NNo, the mind is extremely clever. Why is this? Because the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.06,1:18:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot survive unless it can convince you\Nthat it knows truth. If the ego knows
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.45,1:18:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,truth, you don't need God. You understand that? The ego's\Nposition then is to displace God.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.83,1:18:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,To displace God. And to displace\Nspiritual souls with
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.98,1:18:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,egocentric ones. One thing we've gotten out of consciousness\Nresearch then is a certain sense of humility.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.02,1:18:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,A certain sense of humility. That as convincing as something may be\Nbuttressed by centuries of argument, it can be
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.11,1:18:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,totally fallacious. What is the level of truth?\NTruth is something by which mankind has lived for a thousand years
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.40,1:19:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and you discover that it's only 160.\NPeople sacrifice their lives
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.52,1:19:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,by the millions for that which is not even\Ntrue. By the millions people sacrifice
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.68,1:19:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,their lives for falsehood and illusion.\NWe're the first generation, we're the first generation
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.84,1:19:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that's had a shot at truth. You realize that?\NIf you had the good luck to be a pal of Jesus Christ
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.51,1:19:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,2003 years ago, you got a shot at it.\NYou know how many people were within the province of his
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.24,1:19:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,teachings, within the purview of the Buddha or Jesus\Nor any of the great teachers. Of course, the Vedas have
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.27,1:19:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,been a source of extremely high truth\Nfor close to 10,000 years, but they don't read the
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.52,1:20:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Vedas in Chicago or Cincinnati\Nor London or any place else. You see, when
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.52,1:20:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth did come about by virtue of the inner awareness\Nof some mystic who sometimes got burned at the stake for his
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.52,1:20:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,efforts, it still only\Nhad a local kind of an effect. It only had a local kind of effect.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.52,1:20:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,See what I'm saying? So, you\Nbegin to become very compassionate about the human condition
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.51,1:20:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,itself. Born without fur or hooves\Nor claws or fangs, no way to survive.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.77,1:20:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you take this human being and put it out with\Nno clothes, nothing on, in the middle of woods, how is
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.73,1:20:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,he going to survive? So, you develop compassion\Nfor the human condition, that it does whatever it thinks it has to
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.08,1:21:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,do to survive, because that's been the nature of life since it's\Nbeen on the planet as it evolved, was first
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.08,1:21:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and foremost dedication to one's own survival.\NAnd then, the extrapolation of that orientation
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.11,1:21:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,as it expresses itself in mind. So, the maps that we just looked at\Nthen, are the expression of the animal
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.11,1:21:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,nature as it evolved over the course of time, expressing\Nitself in the intellect, then in politics.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.11,1:21:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, all the maps were within the expression\Nof the primitive animal, how it expresses itself
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.69,1:21:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,politically. You see, the animal nature then\Ndominating whole continents. Whole continents
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.69,1:21:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate 70, 130, 140, 150,\N160, less than John Dillinger.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.03,1:22:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you now develop a compassion, because you see\Nthat which Jesus Christ and the Buddha both taught,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.66,1:22:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is only ignorance, that there is only ignorance.\NAnd Krishna, of the great avatars of all history,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.62,1:22:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,stand for compassion, stand for forgiveness, stand that the only\Nsin possible is coming out of ignorance. Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.85,1:22:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,our generation somehow, now\Nat 207, we have come into a different dominion.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.17,1:22:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The world of consciousness at 207, we live in a different\Nworld than our parents. We live in a different world
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.03,1:22:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,than we ourselves lived in until very recently. Our\Nexpectations of our self have shifted. And spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.38,1:22:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,curiosity, spiritual education\Nhas becoming more and more dominant in our society. The interest in
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.42,1:23:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual issues is now quite strong.\NIn the same time, we've seen the emergence of
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.22,1:23:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,basically purely spiritual, not religious, but purely spiritual\Nteachings reaching the core of society.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.22,1:23:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the 12 steps of\Nwhat started out as AA, now it's the 12 step program which covers
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.28,1:23:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,just about every human condition. You see, the 12 steps have\Nleaked out and pervade all of society. I hear many people on TV
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.28,1:23:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and they'll pull out a phrase and I know exactly that they've been in AA or they got it there.\NIt came right to me, it got out of the 12 steps and the 12 traditions.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.28,1:23:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And then that leads into A Course in Miracles.\NSo you see an evolution of, you see 12 step psychology
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.79,1:23:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and thinking that's pervading business and society\Nin many non-visible ways. Then you see
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.05,1:24:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,going on to the Course in Miracles and you see forgiveness and\Nhow to recontextualize things so that you see them differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.17,1:24:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to transcend the polarity of the opposites, the way to\Ntranscend guilt and anger and hatred of others
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.61,1:24:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is by recontextualization. That a thing looks\Ndifferent when it's recontextualized is beginning to emerge in society.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.63,1:24:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,See, people don't realize that we're having a profound effect.\NOn the news now you hear the word
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.63,1:24:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,perceived. Perceived. See, that perception\Nis one thing and reality is another. The police
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.98,1:24:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,responded to a perceived threat or the victim responded\Nto a perceived. So in court now we have
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.01,1:24:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,introduced the whole concept of perceived. It was\Nperceived that way. We don't say it was that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.04,1:25:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Just jumping into the whole idea of perceived\Nis such an enormous jump. Well that's just the basis of the Course
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.04,1:25:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in Miracles, isn't it? That you ask the Holy Spirit\Nto help you forgive and the way the Holy Spirit does
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.42,1:25:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,it is changes how you see it. The purpose of these\Nmaps this morning about rural governments and all was
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.49,1:25:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to reveal unknown factors. That when you see it differently now\Nyou feel differently about it. Just as those of us that
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.49,1:25:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,just came back from Europe got to look at\NAmerica's political positions from a broader view. How we are
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.94,1:25:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,viewed in Europe, let's say. And it gave us an easier\Ngoing view of it because we could see their thought was
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.94,1:25:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,look, it's their problem. Why try to get us in? Well, yeah, right.\NSo think of it, why not?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.77,1:26:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see, you know, that's sort of common sense. Why drag us into your mess?\NWe've got enough problems of our own with sort of the attitude, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.77,1:26:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But there was no sharp anti-Americanism. Nobody was hostile to Americans.\NNothing like that. And an easy goingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.12,1:26:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So ignorance, if ignorance is the only sin then\Nthe purpose of today's lecture then is to advance our consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.12,1:26:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we're more aware. It changes our perception of the world.\NWe can transcend polarities that we would have gotten caught in before.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.12,1:26:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And we become more forgiving,\Nmore easy going, more loving ourself. And that's
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.22,1:26:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,how world peace comes about because we as a group\Nare profoundly affecting the level of consciousness of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.22,1:26:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You see on that graph of the distribution of consciousness\Nthat at the very far right, the graph
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.60,1:26:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes very slim. Very slim. On the other hand\Nit becomes extremely powerful. There we go.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.14,1:27:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We're back on. Thank you.\NYeah, you see over here, the number of people over here is very few
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.14,1:27:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,population wise. You know, here you're talking about\N87% of the world. And people over here, this audience
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.34,1:27:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,here today, you're only a little bitty slice of the cucumber.\NYou understand? So you got one slice of the cucumber trying to influence
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.34,1:27:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole rest of the cucumber. And it does so\Nby the fact that it's power. So as consciousness advances, it's power
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.43,1:27:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,increases logarithmically. So\Nfor a group like this, for their consciousness to jump even five points
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.91,1:27:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is already influencing the total consciousness of all of mankind.\NAnd so we'll conclude with a break. And then what we're going to do
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.23,1:27:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is we're going to answer questions. We're going to talk to people.\NAnd what we discovered is when we meet
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.23,1:28:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,people and talk to them, we'll leave the audio on.\NSo the whole audience shares, you know? And you can come up and ask me individually
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.23,1:28:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'll greet and hug you all. And try to answer every individual question.\NBut we'll all share it together. Okay? Will that be an alright thing to do?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.23,1:28:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So you want to take a ten minute break? Your minds must be exhausted\Nby now.
